# ForgeOS Architecture

ForgeOS is a multi-tenant Industrial Operating System for manufacturing SMEs. JH Gomes is the first deployment customer, not the product architecture.

## Principles

- Architecture-first development; smallest safe change.
- Reusable core stays customer-neutral — no JH Gomes-specific hardcoding in global modules.
- Every business record is tenant-scoped; enforce tenant isolation in queries, APIs, and UI.
- Internal naming (code, DB fields, API routes) is English; user-facing text uses i18n dictionaries (`pt-PT`, `en`).

## Protected areas (require explicit approval)

- Authentication and session handling
- Row-level security and database migrations (`supabase/migrations/`)
- Billing and infrastructure
- Secrets and environment configuration

